Interview an individual in class that may have some cultural differences.

Sean Stapleton

    What is the cultural group of the person that you interviewed? 
      Taoism

    
    What are Surface Culture aspects from this person's culture that you appreciate?
      Practicing meditation, also practicing respect of all individuals and ridding judgment


    
    What are some unspoken rules about this culture that you learned about?
      Living in harmony with nature; living in simplicity


    
    What are some deeply held beliefs that you learned about?
      Thinking of life as a drop in the ocean which helps think that life isn't worth worrying about, believes that in death consciousness
      continues without body in some form


    

Debrief and write about the following:

    Why is it important to learn about other cultures? And, how might this help you in future interactions?
    What do you do when you meet someone at school or work whose culture appears to differ from your own?

     3. How would you describe a company culture that you would be proud to be a part of?
